# PowerShell Compatibility Rules

## Command Standards
- **ALWAYS** use PowerShell-friendly commands
- **NEVER** use '&&' operator for command chaining
- **ALWAYS** use ';' or separate commands instead
- **ALWAYS** run commands in background when appropriate

## Error Handling
- **ALWAYS** provide honest, factual reports
- **NEVER** make assumptions or guess
- **ALWAYS** ask clarifying questions when unclear
- **NEVER** skip studying the actual codebase

## Performance Standards
- **ALWAYS** optimize for speed and efficiency
- **NEVER** over-engineer solutions
- **ALWAYS** prefer simple, straightforward implementations
- **NEVER** compromise on performance metrics